column8: T-cell epitopes in severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS) coronavirus spike protein elicit a specific T-cell immune response in patients who recover from SARS.

column5: Yue-Dan Wang; Wei Feng Chen
column8: Detecting specific cytotoxic T lymphocytes against SARS-coronavirus with DimerX HLA-A2:Ig fusion protein.
column117: PBMC from HLA-A2 -negative SARS-recovered donors and healthy HLA-A2-positive donors showed no response in the assay.  No response was found to a negative control peptide derived from the homologous sequence in HcoV-229e (H1121 [ISVVLIFVV]).

column5: Yue-Dan Wang; Wei Feng Chen
column8: Detecting specific cytotoxic T lymphocytes against SARS-coronavirus with DimerX HLA-A2:Ig fusion protein.
column117: DimerX-based flow cytometry staining was used to screen PBMC from SARS donors.  PBMC from HLA-A2 -negative SARS-recovered donors and healthy HLA-A2-positive donors showed no response in the assay.  No response was found to a negative control peptide derived from the homologous sequence in HcoV-229e (H1121 [ISVVLIFVV]).

column5: Baomei Wang; Huabiao Chen; Xiaodong Jiang; Minghui Zhang; Tao Wan; Nan Li; Xiangyang Zhou; Yanfeng Wu; Feng Yang; Yizhi Yu; Xiaoning Wang; Ruifu Yang; Xuetao Cao
column8: Identification of an HLA-A*0201-restricted CD8+ T-cell epitope SSp-1 of SARS-CoV spike protein.
column83: Lymphocytes  from healthy donors were stimulated with peptide-pulsed dendritic cells in the presence of IL-7 and IL-10 weekly for 4 weeks.
column117: The response was shown to be dose-dependent, with peptide doses of 1, 10, and 100 micrograms/mL.  The response was greater with higher concentrations.  A similar response was shown using peptide-pulsed T2 cells as target cells.

column5: Huabiao Chen; Jinlin Hou; Xiaodong Jiang; Shiwu Ma; Minjie Meng; Baomei Wang; Minghui Zhang; Mingxia Zhang; Xiaoping Tang; Fuchun Zhang; Tao Wan; Nan Li; Yizhi Yu; Hongbo Hu; Ruifu Yang; Wei He; Xiaoning Wang; Xuetao Cao
column8: Response of memory CD8+ T cells to severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS) coronavirus in recovered SARS patients and healthy individuals.
column83: SARS patients were SARS-CoV-seropositive and 12-14 months post-recovery.  PBMC were incubated with heat inactivated SARS-CoV to generate SARS-CoV CTLs.
column117: Tetramer staining of CTLs from recovered SARS patients peaked 7 days after in vitro restimulation with heat inactivated SARS-CoV. Tetramer positive cells were also CD45RA+, CCR5+, CD44+, CD62L-, and CCR7-.

column5: Huabiao Chen; Jinlin Hou; Xiaodong Jiang; Shiwu Ma; Minjie Meng; Baomei Wang; Minghui Zhang; Mingxia Zhang; Xiaoping Tang; Fuchun Zhang; Tao Wan; Nan Li; Yizhi Yu; Hongbo Hu; Ruifu Yang; Wei He; Xiaoning Wang; Xuetao Cao
column8: Response of memory CD8+ T cells to severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS) coronavirus in recovered SARS patients and healthy individuals.
column117: Tetramer staining of CTLs from healthy donors was positive in 5 out of 36 subjects and peaked 7 days after in vitro stimulation with heat inactivated SARS-CoV. Tetramer binding was of lower avidity than the binding observed in CTLs derived from SARS recovered patients. Tetramer positive cells were also CD45RA+, CCR5+, CD44+, CD62L-, and CCR7-.

column5: Huabiao Chen; Jinlin Hou; Xiaodong Jiang; Shiwu Ma; Minjie Meng; Baomei Wang; Minghui Zhang; Mingxia Zhang; Xiaoping Tang; Fuchun Zhang; Tao Wan; Nan Li; Yizhi Yu; Hongbo Hu; Ruifu Yang; Wei He; Xiaoning Wang; Xuetao Cao
column8: Response of memory CD8+ T cells to severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS) coronavirus in recovered SARS patients and healthy individuals.
column83: SARS patients were SARS-CoV-seropositive and 12-14 months post-recovery.  PBMC were restimulated with heat inactivated SARS-CoV.
column117: Heat-inactivated SARS-CoV restimulated PBMC from recovered SARS patients produced a greater level of IFNg and TNFa in response to the epitope than did healthy donors (also by ELISPOT). PBMC from recovered SARS patients also produced perforin and granzyme A in higher levels than healthy donor PBMC.

column5: Huabiao Chen; Jinlin Hou; Xiaodong Jiang; Shiwu Ma; Minjie Meng; Baomei Wang; Minghui Zhang; Mingxia Zhang; Xiaoping Tang; Fuchun Zhang; Tao Wan; Nan Li; Yizhi Yu; Hongbo Hu; Ruifu Yang; Wei He; Xiaoning Wang; Xuetao Cao
column8: Response of memory CD8+ T cells to severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS) coronavirus in recovered SARS patients and healthy individuals.
column117: Heat-inactivated SARS-CoV stimulated PBMC from healthy donors produced IFNg and TNFa in response to the epitope, however,  they produced a lower amount than PBMC from recovered SARS-CoV patients (also by ELISPOT). Healthy donor PBMC also produced perforin and granzyme A in lower levels than PBMC from recovered SARS patients.

column5: Huabiao Chen; Jinlin Hou; Xiaodong Jiang; Shiwu Ma; Minjie Meng; Baomei Wang; Minghui Zhang; Mingxia Zhang; Xiaoping Tang; Fuchun Zhang; Tao Wan; Nan Li; Yizhi Yu; Hongbo Hu; Ruifu Yang; Wei He; Xiaoning Wang; Xuetao Cao
column8: Response of memory CD8+ T cells to severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS) coronavirus in recovered SARS patients and healthy individuals.
column83: SARS patients were SARS-CoV-seropositive and 12-14 months post-recovery.  PBMC were incubated with heat inactivated SARS-CoV to generate SARS-CoV CTLs prior to tetramer staining.
column117: SSp-1 specific CTLs isolated by peptide-tetramer staining from recovered SARS patients lysed target cells presenting spike protein more efficiently than SSp-1 specific CTLs derived from healthy donors. These CTLS also produced IFNg ( ELISPOT) in response to epitope more efficiently than SSp-1 specific CTLs derived from healthy donors.

column83: Five HLA-A*0201 healthy donors with no history of SARS-CoV infection were used as controls.  In vitro restimulation of adherent cells was done with recombinant N protein.
